{"id":"338738522_How_Should_Clinicians_Integrate_Mental_Health_Into_Epidemic_Responses","abstract":"The 2014 Ebola epidemic in Sierra Leone and the current outbreak that began in 2018 in the Democratic Republic of the Congo generated numerous mental health crises that remain unaddressed by global standard infectious disease protocols. This article explores how responders should integrate mental health care into standard Ebola care.","authors":["Shantanu Srivatsa","Kearsley Stewart"],"meta":["January 2020","DOI:10.1001/amajethics.2020.10"],"references":["331586652_Post-Ebola_psychosocial_Experiences_and_coping_mechanisms_among_Ebola_survivors_a_systematic_review","330839796_Assessing_reporting_delays_and_the_effective_reproduction_number_The_2018-19_Ebola_epidemic_in_DRC_May_2018-January_2019","325942889_Fear_and_culture_Contextualising_mental_health_impact_of_the_2014-2016_Ebola_epidemic_in_West_Africa","323833444_Impact_of_Ebola_experiences_and_risk_perceptions_on_mental_health_in_Sierra_Leone_July_2015","316733750_Neuropsychological_long-term_sequelae_of_Ebola_virus_disease_survivors_-_A_systematic_review","333649098_Responding_to_the_Ebola_virus_disease_outbreak_in_DR_Congo_when_will_we_learn_from_Sierra_Leone","332050402_Institutional_trust_and_misinformation_in_the_response_to_the_2018-19_Ebola_outbreak_in_North_Kivu_DR_Congo_a_population-based_survey","326077839_Outbreak_of_Ebola_virus_disease_in_the_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo_April-May_2018_an_epidemiological_study","317085111_Community-Based_Participatory_Research_Studies_on_HIVAIDS_Prevention_2005-2014","316074046_Validated_Screening_Tools_for_Common_Mental_Disorders_in_Low_and_Middle_Income_Countries_A_Systematic_Review"]}